title: Levi’s Has Dropped a Collection of Merch Celebrating Nas: Shop It Now
summary: The capsule includes three pieces in celebration of the rapper's exceptional career.
body: All products and services featured are independently chosen by editors. However, Billboard may receive a commission on orders placed through its retail links, and the retailer may receive certain auditable data for accounting purposes. One of hip-hop’s greats was just immortalized on Levi’s most iconic silhouettes. Levi’s latest collection aims at celebrating Nas, the Brooklyn native who took the rap game by storm with Billboard chart-topping hits such as “I’m Gonna Be Alright” and “Hot Boyz.” Nas has 17 Grammy nominations and one win to date, and was ranked as No. 3 on Billboard ‘s 10 Best Rappers of All Time list. The “N.Y. State of Mind” rapper even has his own record label, Mass Appeal Records. It’s safe to say that Nas’ career is one worth celebrating, and it seems Levi’s agrees. The aforementioned Nas collection features three pieces, two tees and one crewneck, all available now on Levi’s website . title: Normani & Two-Time Olympian Jordan Chiles Switch Roles In New ‘Switching Stages’ Episode
summary: The Olympic athlete and music powerhouse take a walk in each other's shoes in the latest episode.
body: In the second episode of Billboard and The Players’ Tribune’s video series Switching Stages, Normani and Two-Time Olympian Jordan Chiles take turns stepping into each other’s shoes for the day. Normani is no stranger to gymnastics, so had the opportunity to perform sophisticated cartwheels and aerials on the beam while Jordan helped her utilize some expert-level technique and form. Elsewhere, the pair stepped into Normani’s world, and learned some tight choreography to Normani’s song “All Yours.” “I actually feel inspired to continue to get back into the gym,” Normani told Jordan after their afternoon together. “You actually inspired me to start dancing,” Jordan replied before going in for a high five. The second episode of Switching Stages comes after Atlanta Hawks point guard Trae Young and Grammy-nominated rapper Quavo spent some time sharing nostalgic stories of growing up in Atlanta. The two stars traded skills from the basketball court to the recording studio, with their studio session laying the foundation for Trae’s rap debut in the duo’s new record “Where I Stay” with 2 Chainz. “Music and sports have always…

title: Ice Spice Uses ‘Pretty Privilege’ to Her Advantage in Fashion-Forward Music Video
summary: She follows up the release of her "Baddie Baddie" track with a new single.
body: Six weeks after releasing her “Baddie Baddie” track , Ice Spice returned on Wednesday (Nov. 5) with “Pretty Privilege,” which could signal that her Y2K! follow-up isn’t far away in 2026. Ice reunites with frequent collaborator RIOTUSA on the production side for the trippy drill-leaning tune. The Bronx native cycles through her typical themes as she addresses the haters, flaunts her looks, deep pockets and how you’ll never hit. “Pretty Privilege, that’s a perk/ I can’t help it, I’m a flirt/ Fine s—t, that’s a fact/ From the front, you see the back/ PR said no clappin’ back, mwah,” she raps to close out the track. Ice Spice also released an accompanying lavish visual for “Pretty Privilege,” and the rapper’s wardrobe didn’t disappoint in the fashion-forward video. Switching into a pink bob wig, Ice twerks on a balcony and then brings out a white couture dress as she flexes in front of her suburban mansion tucked away in the woods.
